Because every `&lt;li&gt;` is wrapped in its own `&lt;ol&gt;`, meaning each one will start at `A`

Instead, use one `&lt;ol&gt;` and add the `&lt;li&gt;` items within it...

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;ol type=&quot;A&quot;&gt;
      &lt;script&gt;
      salad = new Array();
      salad[0]=&quot;feta&quot;;
      salad[1]=&quot;tomatoes&quot;;
      salad[2]=&quot;lettuce&quot;;
      salad[3]=&quot;olives&quot;; 
      salad[4]=&quot;olive oil&quot;;   
      salad[5]=&quot;vinegar&quot;;
      salad[6]=&quot;herbs&quot;; 
      salad[7]=&quot;seasoning&quot;; 
      for (i=0;i&lt;salad.length;i=i+1) {
        document.writeln(&quot;&lt;li&gt;&quot; + salad[i] + &quot;&lt;/li&gt;&quot;);
      }
      &lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

You have to take the `ol` element *out of the loop*, as a wrapper for your list script. Otherwise the loop will create a new `ol` every time, always starting with &quot;A&quot;:

